    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-11-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-11-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="849"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d849">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Baron <persName
                            type="to">Fava</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-11-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 27, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear</hi> Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Ambassador</hi>:
                    Answering your personal communication of the 26th, I have the pleasure to inform
                    you that the subject of the Tallulah lynchings and the question of providing a
                    Federal forum for such cases, concerning which you have heretofore conferred
                    with me, have been duty considered by the President and will be appropriately
                    treated in his forthcoming message.</p>
                <p>Believe me to be, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
